With fears the third wave of COVID-19 is upon us, the country's vaccine rollout is simply not where it should have been, with government missing some of its own deadlines. eNCA’s Heidi Giokos reports. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - One Johannesburg vaccination centre says it's prepared to handle the influx of people wanting to get vaccinated when Phase Two of the COVID-19 vaccination rollout programme kicks off on Monday. With fears the third wave of COVID-19 is upon us, the country's vaccine rollout is simply not where it should have been, with the government missing some deadlines. READ: COVID-19 Vaccine: Senior citizens urged to register Fewer than half a million healthcare workers have been vaccinated, and there are 1.5 million who need to get the jab. Watch the video above for more details on this story.